// useIsMobile
// Detects whether the current viewport is a mobile-width screen (< 640px).

Uses matchMedia("(max-width: 639px)") and updates state when the viewport crosses the breakpoint.
Initializes synchronously from the current viewport size to avoid a flash of wrong layout.
Gracefully handles SSR (no window) and browsers without matchMedia support.

FUNCTION useIsMobile() -> boolean                                               EXPORT
  Manages state: isMobile, initialized from the current matchMedia result.
  On mount, adds a "change" listener to the media query to keep isMobile in sync with viewport width.
  On unmount, removes the listener.
